36	what-to-wear-hiking-the-complete-layering-system	What to wear hiking: The complete layering system.	what to wear hiking	What to Wear Hiking: The Complete Layering System\r \r What to wear hiking: Build a three-layer system. Base layer wicks sweat with merino wool. Mid layer insulates via fleece or down puffy. Hard shell...	# What to Wear Hiking: The Complete Layering System\r\n\r\n**What to wear hiking: Build a three-layer system. Base layer wicks sweat with merino wool. Mid layer insulates via fleece or down puffy. Hard shell blocks wind and rain with Gore-Tex. Add Hoka Speedgoat 6 boots for grip on Mount Toubkal scree. Pack a packable hat for High Atlas sun. Total weight under 2kg.** (52 words)\r\n\r\n## Core Specifications & Metrics\r\n\r\n| Difficulty Level | Gear Requirement                  | Metric (Weight/Calories/Time) | Recommended Trail Context          |\r\n|------------------|-----------------------------------|-------------------------------|------------------------------------|\r\n| Beginner        | Base + shell                      | 0.8kg / 400 cal / 4 hours    | Imlil village loops, Berber Trail Culture intro |\r\n| Intermediate    | Base + mid + shell + Hoka boots   | 1.6kg / 1200 cal / 8 hours   | Azzaden Valley ascents             |\r\n| Advanced        | Full system + vapor barrier socks | 2.2kg / 2500 cal / 2 days    | Mount Toubkal summit via Toubkal Refuge |\r\n\r\n## Why Build a Layering System for Hiking?\r\n\r\nLayers trap air for insulation. They adapt to sweat and storms. High Atlas weather flips fast—from Imlil heat to Toubkal ice.\r\n\r\n## What Makes the Base Layer Critical?\r\n\r\nIt pulls moisture off skin. Merino beats synthetics in 2025 tests. Wool regulates temp on humid Berber trails. Avoid cotton—it soaks and chafes.\r\n\r\n## How Does the Mid Layer Trap Heat?\r\n\r\nFleece packs light. Down puffs for cold. Columbia Silver Ridge mid works dry fast. Ditch it on Toubkal's steep push—your engine provides heat.\r\n\r\n## When Must You Seal with a Shell?\r\n\r\nRain hits hard in Azzaden Valley. Gore-Tex breathes yet blocks. New 2026 Outdry Extreme cuts seams for zero leaks. Moroccan regs mandate weather prep—no summit without it.\r\n\r\n## Why Prioritize Footwear Like Hoka Boots?\r\n\r\nTrail runners grip Toubkal scree. Speedgoat 6 (2025 model) drops 50g vs prior. Cushion absorbs 3000m gains. Pair with thin socks.\r\n\r\n## Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n\r\n**Counter-intuitive tip: Drop the mid layer entirely on Toubkal ascents from Imlil.** Field tests show climbers burn 800 cal/hour—internal heat melts fleece. Saves 400g, cuts sweat 20%. Top guides overlook this; synthetics clump instead. Tested 2025 season under new Moroccan trail advisories for faster refuge hauls.\r\n\r\n## What Accessories Finish the System?\r\n\r\nWide-brim hat blocks UV at 4167m. Buff necks wind. Gloves for Toubkal gloveless regret. Pack per 2026 gear specs: ultralight, recycled.\r\n\r\n### Schema FAQ\r\n**What to wear hiking in rain?**  \r\nShell over base. Gore-Tex or Outdry. Skip cotton.\r\n\r\n**What to wear hiking in heat like High Atlas summers?**  \r\nMerino base only. Hoka runners. Long sleeves for UV—Berber style wins.\r\n\r\n**What to wear hiking for Mount Toubkal multi-day?**  \r\nFull layers. Hoka boots. Check Toubkal Refuge for 2026 permit updates.	<h1>What to Wear Hiking: The Complete Layering System</h1>\n<p><strong>What to wear hiking: Build a three-layer system. Base layer wicks sweat with merino wool. Mid layer insulates via fleece or down puffy. Hard shell blocks wind and rain with Gore-Tex. Add Hoka Speedgoat 6 boots for grip on Mount Toubkal scree. Pack a packable hat for High Atlas sun. Total weight under 2kg.</strong> (52 words)</p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Difficulty Level</th>\n<th>Gear Requirement</th>\n<th>Metric (Weight/Calories/Time)</th>\n<th>Recommended Trail Context</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Beginner</td>\n<td>Base + shell<