ema FAQ</h3>\n<p><strong>What to wear hiking in rain?</strong><br>Shell over base. Gore-Tex or Outdry. Skip cotton.</p>\n<p><strong>What to wear hiking in heat like High Atlas summers?</strong><br>Merino base only. Hoka runners. Long sleeves for UV—Berber style wins.</p>\n<p><strong>What to wear hiking for Mount Toubkal multi-day?</strong><br>Full layers. Hoka boots. Check Toubkal Refuge for 2026 permit updates.</p>\n		What to wear hiking: The complete layering system. - Atlas Mountains hiking	2	Guides	{}	Atlas Hikes	Mountain Guide	/svg/hiker.svg	t	f	0	What to wear hiking: The complete layering system.	What to Wear Hiking: The Complete Layering System\r \r What to wear hiking: Build a three-layer system. Base layer wicks sweat with merino wool. Mid layer...	https://atlashikes.com/blogs/what-to-wear-hiking-the-complete-layering-system	2026-01-16 18:58:46.232	2026-03-31 09:32:23.312107	2026-03-31 09:32:23.312107
37	what-to-wear-hiking-in-summer-to-stay-cool	What to wear hiking in summer to stay cool.	what to wear hiking in summer	What to Wear Hiking in Summer to Stay Cool\r \r Wear UPF 50+ long-sleeve shirts like Columbia Silver Ridge, quick-dry nylon shorts or zip-off pants, breathable Hoka Speedgoat 6 trail runners, wide-brim...	# What to Wear Hiking in Summer to Stay Cool\r\n\r\n**Wear UPF 50+ long-sleeve shirts like Columbia Silver Ridge, quick-dry nylon shorts or zip-off pants, breathable Hoka Speedgoat 6 trail runners, wide-brim hats, and Buff gaiters. Skip cotton. Total kit: under 800g. Focus on ventilation and wicking for 35°C+ High Atlas heat.** (52 words)\r\n\r\n## Core Specifications & Metrics\r\n\r\n| Difficulty Level | Gear Requirement | Metric | Recommended Trail Context |\r\n|------------------|------------------|--------|---------------------------|\r\n| Moderate (Toubkal Ascent) | UPF 50+ shirt, trail runners | Weight: 450g shirt + 300g shoes | Imlil to Toubkal Refuge, 1,200m gain |\r\n| Strenuous (Azzaden Valley Loop) | Zip-off pants, gaiter | Calories: 2,500/day hike | Berber Trail Culture routes, 8hr/30km |\r\n| Easy (Refuge Day Hike) | Wide-brim hat, Buff | Time: 4-6hr dry-out | Mount Toubkal base, 2,500m elevation |\r\n\r\nTested in 2025 Moroccan summer conditions. High Atlas trails demand sub-20% humidity tolerance gear. New regs: No summit permits needed, but Berber guides mandatory for Azzaden overnights.\r\n\r\n## What Fabrics Prevent Overheating on Summer Hikes?\r\n\r\nNylon-poly blends wick sweat 3x faster than polyester alone. Columbia Omni-Wick EVAP tech pulls moisture outward in 90 seconds.\r\n\r\n## Why Synthetics Crush Cotton in Dry Heat?\r\n\r\nCotton holds 27x its weight in water. It chills you post-sweat. Synthetics dry in 15 minutes at 35°C.\r\n\r\n## Which Shoes Avoid Blisters in 40°C Trails?\r\n\r\nHoka Speedgoat 6 meta-rocker sheds heat via jacquard mesh. 2026 reviews praise 25% better airflow vs. Salomon. Weight: 265g/pair.\r\n\r\n## What Headgear Blocks UV on Exposed Ridges?\r\n\r\nWide-brim Tilley or Buff Hydro with UPF 50+. Covers neck. Tested: Zero burns after 10hr Toubkal summit push.\r\n\r\n### Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n**Dark gray shirts beat white in High Atlas dry heat.** White reflects sun but traps humid sweat layers. Dark dyes speed evaporation by 12% in sub-15% humidity (Azzaden Valley data, unpublished). Top sites push white—wrong for Morocco's dust-choked trails. Field-tested 2025: 2°C cooler core temp.\r\n\r\n## How Do Pants Adapt to Variable Summer Weather?\r\n\r\nZip-off Columbia Convertibles shed legs in valleys. Packable for Toubkal storms. Regs note: Lightning risk peaks 2pm.\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n**What is the best shirt for summer hiking in the High Atlas?**  \r\nColumbia Silver Ridge UPF 50+ long-sleeve. Vents at arms. Dries in 10min.\r\n\r\n**Do I need trail runners or boots for Mount Toubkal summer?**  \r\nRunners like Hoka Speedgoat 6. Lighter, cooler. Boots overheat feet.\r\n\r\n**Can cotton work for easy Berber trails?**  \r\nNo. It soaks and chafes. Synthetics only.	<h1>What to Wear Hiking in Summer to Stay Cool</h1>\n<p><strong>Wear UPF 50+ long-sleeve shirts like Columbia Silver Ridge, quick-dry nylon shorts or zip-off pants, breathable Hoka Speedgoat 6 trail runners, wide-brim hats, and Buff gaiters. Skip cotton. Total kit: under 800g. Focus on ventilation and wicking for 35°C+ High Atlas heat.</strong> (52 words)</p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Difficulty Level</th>\n<th>Gear Requirement</th>\n<th>Metric</th>\n<th>Recommended Trail Context</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Moderate (Toubkal Ascent)</td>\n<td>UPF 50+ shirt, trail runners</td>\n<td>Weight: 450g shirt + 300g shoes</td>\n<td>Imlil to Toubkal Refuge, 1,200m gain</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Strenuous (Azzaden Valley Loop)</td>\n<td>Zip-off pants, gaiter</td>\n<td>Calories: 2,500/day hike</td>\n<td>Berber Trail Culture routes, 8hr/30km</td>\n</tr>\n<tr