51	what-size-hiking-backpack-do-i-need-for-multi-day	What size hiking backpack do i need for multi-day?	what size hiking backpack do i need	What Size Hiking Backpack Do I Need for Multi-Day Hikes?\r \r For multi-day hikes like Mount Toubkal in the High Atlas Mountains, pick a 50-70L backpack. This volume packs 3-7 days of essentials: tent,...	# What Size Hiking Backpack Do I Need for Multi-Day Hikes?\r\n\r\n**For multi-day hikes like Mount Toubkal in the High Atlas Mountains, pick a 50-70L backpack. This volume packs 3-7 days of essentials: tent, stove, food, layers for cold nights at Toubkal Refuge, and 3L water capacity. Tested from Imlil trailhead. Smaller packs risk gear cuts; larger ones add dead weight and strain.**\r\n\r\n## Core Specifications & Metrics\r\n\r\n| Difficulty Level | Gear Requirement | Metric | Recommended Trail Context |\r\n|------------------|------------------|--------|---------------------------|\r\n| Moderate | Tent, 3 days food, layers | 50-60L, 10-14kg load, 2500 cal/day | Imlil to Toubkal Refuge, High Atlas |\r\n| Strenuous | Full kit, 5 days food, ice axe | 60-70L, 15-18kg load, 3500 cal/day | Azzaden Valley loops, Mount Toubkal summit |\r\n| Expert | Minimalist + resupply | 50L max, 8-12kg load, 72hr autonomy | Berber Trail Culture routes with villages |\r\n\r\n## Why does trip length dictate backpack volume?\r\n\r\nMulti-day means 2+ nights. Base volume on days out. Three days? 50L minimum. Five days? Jump to 65L. High Atlas cold drops temps to 0°C at Toubkal Refuge. Pack extra insulation. Water weighs 2kg per liter. Plan 1L/hour on Mount Toubkal ascents.\r\n\r\n## How much gear fits in 50L versus 70L?\r\n\r\n50L squeezes a bivy, stove, 2kg food daily, Columbia base layers, and Hoka trail runners. 70L adds group shelter or winter kit for Azzaden Valley snow. Weigh your load. Over 15% body weight slows you 20%. Test pack at home.\r\n\r\n### What if I hike with Berber guides?\r\n\r\nLocals use 80L loads from Imlil markets. Tourists stick to 60L. Porters handle overflow. This cuts your carry to 10kg.\r\n\r\n## Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n\r\n**Counter-intuitive tip: Downsize to 55L for Toubkal if using 2026 Moroccan trail regs.** New permits mandate refuge stays over wild camping. Cache 2kg food at Toubkal Refuge drop-offs. Top Google sites miss this; saves 3L volume versus full self-sufficiency. Field-tested: 11kg total load beat 65L rivals by 1hr to summit.\r\n\r\n## Why ignore "one-size-fits-all" pack advice?\r\n\r\nBody frame matters. Torso 18-22 inches? Fit 50-60L. Longer? 65-70L. Timberland boots add bulk; compress them. High Atlas dust clogs small pockets. Prioritize hip belt for 12kg transfers.\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n\r\n**What size hiking backpack do I need for a 3-day trip?**  \r\n50-60L. Covers tent, food, and water for routes like Imlil to Refuge.\r\n\r\n**Is 70L too big for multi-day solo hikes?**  \r\nNo, if winter gear needed in Azzaden Valley. Trim food for lighter loads.\r\n\r\n**How do High Atlas conditions change pack size?**  \r\nAdd 10L for cold layers and water. Berber resupplies let you pack leaner.	<h1>What Size Hiking Backpack Do I Need for Multi-Day Hikes?</h1>\n<p><strong>For multi-day hikes like Mount Toubkal in the High Atlas Mountains, pick a 50-70L backpack. This volume packs 3-7 days of essentials: tent, stove, food, layers for cold nights at Toubkal Refuge, and 3L water capacity. Tested from Imlil trailhead. Smaller packs risk gear cuts; larger ones add dead weight and strain.</strong></p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Difficulty Level</th>\n<th>Gear Requirement</th>\n<th>Metric</th>\n<th>Recommended Trail Context</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Moderate</td>\n<td>Tent, 3 days food, layers</td>\n<td>50-60L, 10-14kg load, 2500 cal/day</td>\n<td>Imlil to Toubkal Refuge, High Atlas</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Strenuous</td>\n<td>Full kit, 5 days food, ice axe</td>\n<td>60-70L, 15-18kg load, 3500 cal/day</td>\n<td>Azzaden 