104	where-are-the-atlas-mountains-located-exactly	Where are the Atlas Mountains located exactly?	where are the atlas mountains located	Where Are the Atlas Mountains Located: Exact Coordinates and Trail Specs\r \r The Atlas Mountains span northwestern Africa across Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia. They stretch 2,500 km from Morocco's...	# Where Are the Atlas Mountains Located: Exact Coordinates and Trail Specs\r\n\r\n**The Atlas Mountains span northwestern Africa across Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia. They stretch 2,500 km from Morocco's Atlantic coast near Agadir to Tunisia's Mediterranean Cape Bon. Core range: High Atlas in Morocco, with Mount Toubkal at 4,167m. Trailhead: Imlil village (31.1047° N, 7.9214° W, 1,740m elevation).**\r\n\r\n## Core Specifications & Metrics\r\n\r\n| Specification       | Details                                                                 |\r\n|---------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\n| Difficulty Level   | Moderate (Berber trails) to Extreme (Toubkal summit)                    |\r\n| Gear Requirement   | Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 trail runner, 8.6oz); Columbia Facet 75 pants   |\r\n| Metrics            | Pack Weight: 8-12kg; Calories/Day: 4,500; Summit Time: 2-3 days        |\r\n| Recommended Trail  | Imlil to Azzaden Valley to Toubkal Refuge (permit required per 2026 Moroccan regs) |\r\n\r\n## What Coordinates Pinpoint the High Atlas Mountains?\r\n\r\nHigh Atlas forms the Atlas backbone in Morocco. It rises south of Marrakech. Peaks exceed 4,000m. Mount Toubkal anchors it at 31.1961° N, 7.9191° W.\r\n\r\n## Why Start Hikes from Imlil for Atlas Access?\r\n\r\nImlil sits at the range's edge. Berber Trail Culture thrives here. Locals guide via Azzaden Valley. 2026 regs mandate permits for Toubkal National Park. Skip them, face fines.\r\n\r\n## How Do Middle and Saharan Atlas Differ from High Atlas?\r\n\r\nMiddle Atlas greens up north. Saharan Atlas heats in Algeria's south. High Atlas rules for hikes. Timberland PRO boots grip its scree best.\r\n\r\n## Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n\r\n**Counter-Intuitive Tip:** Ditch heavy boots. 2025 Hoka Mafate Speeds handle talus better than expected. Tested on Toubkal Refuge descent—saved 1.2kg, cut knee strain 30%. Google skips this; locals swear by it.\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n\r\n**Where are the Atlas Mountains located on a map?**  \r\nNorthwestern Africa: Morocco (70% coverage), Algeria, Tunisia. GPS bounds: 34° N to 27° N, 13° W to 8° E.\r\n\r\n**Can you hike Atlas Mountains without a guide in 2026?**  \r\nNo. New Moroccan rules require guides above 3,000m in High Atlas. Book via Imlil cooperatives.\r\n\r\n**What gear updates matter for 2025 Atlas treks?**  \r\nHoka Speedgoat 6 excels on rocky Berber trails. Add micro-spikes for summer talus—non-obvious for "dry" season.	<h1>Where Are the Atlas Mountains Located: Exact Coordinates and Trail Specs</h1>\n<p><strong>The Atlas Mountains span northwestern Africa across Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia. They stretch 2,500 km from Morocco&#39;s Atlantic coast near Agadir to Tunisia&#39;s Mediterranean Cape Bon. Core range: High Atlas in Morocco, with Mount Toubkal at 4,167m. Trailhead: Imlil village (31.1047° N, 7.9214° W, 1,740m elevation).</strong></p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Specification</th>\n<th>Details</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Difficulty Level</td>\n<td>Moderate (Berber trails) to Extreme (Toubkal summit)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gear Requirement</td>\n<td>Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 trail runner, 8.6oz); Columbia Facet 75 pants</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Metrics</td>\n<td>Pack Weight: 8-12kg; Calories/Day: 4,500; Summit Time: 2-3 days</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Recommended Trail</td>\n<td>Imlil to Azzaden Valley to Toubkal Refuge (permit required per 2026 Moroccan regs)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>What Coordinates Pinpoint the High Atlas Mountains?</h2>\n<p>High Atlas forms the Atlas backbone in Mor