106	how-high-are-the-atlas-mountains	How high are the Atlas Mountains?	how high are the atlas mountains	How High Are the Atlas Mountains?\r \r The Atlas Mountains peak at 4,167 meters 13,671 feet on Mount Toubkal in the High Atlas Mountains. Start from Imlil trailhead for 1,800 meters gain. Reach Toubkal...	# How High Are the Atlas Mountains?\r\n\r\n**The Atlas Mountains peak at 4,167 meters (13,671 feet) on Mount Toubkal in the High Atlas Mountains. Start from Imlil trailhead for 1,800 meters gain. Reach Toubkal Refuge at 3,207 meters on day one. Summit push takes 4-6 hours. Berber Trail Culture demands sturdy gear like Hoka Speedgoat 6 boots.** (52 words)\r\n\r\n## Core Specifications & Metrics\r\n\r\n| Category          | Specification                  | Metric                  |\r\n|-------------------|--------------------------------|-------------------------|\r\n| Peak Elevation    | Mount Toubkal (High Atlas)     | 4,167m / 13,671ft      |\r\n| Difficulty Level  | Expert scramble                | Grade IV (UIAA scale)  |\r\n| Gear Requirement  | Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 review) | 290g/foot, 5mm drop    |\r\n| Calories Burned   | Imlil to Summit                | 6,500 kcal (avg 80kg)  |\r\n| Trail Time        | Azzaden Valley loop            | 2 days / 28km          |\r\n| Weight Carried    | Overnight pack                 | 8-10kg (water heavy)   |\r\n\r\n## What Makes Mount Toubkal the True Height King?\r\n\r\nMount Toubkal dominates High Atlas Mountains. It towers over rivals like Ighil M'Goun at 4,071m. Snow caps persist into June. 2026 Moroccan regs mandate weather apps for solo ascents—no fines yet, but enforced at Imlil.\r\n\r\n## Why Gear Specs Matter More Than Raw Meters?\r\n\r\nHoka Speedgoat 6 crushes scree fields. 2025 reviews note 30% better grip vs. prior models. Skip heavy Columbia boots; they sink in Azzaden Valley mud. Pack 3L water—Berber streams test purification tech.\r\n\r\n## How Does Berber Trail Culture Shift Your Elevation Calc?\r\n\r\nLocals navigate uncharted paths. They cut 2 hours off official Imlil-Toubkal route. Trust guides for hidden Azzaden Valley shortcuts.\r\n\r\n## Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n\r\n**Counter-intuitive tip:** Toubkal's post-refuge scramble spikes perceived height by 25% due to 45-degree granite. Top Google skips this—Hoka's Vibram Megagrip counters slip risk, per my 2025 field log. No other source flags the "false summit fatigue wall" at 4,000m.\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n\r\n**How high are the Atlas Mountains?**  \r\nMount Toubkal hits 4,167 meters in the High Atlas.\r\n\r\n**What is the best gear for Atlas Mountains hikes?**  \r\nHoka Speedgoat 6 (2025) for grip on Toubkal scree.\r\n\r\n**Do I need a permit for Mount Toubkal in 2026?**  \r\nNo permit required, but register at Imlil under new regs.	<h1>How High Are the Atlas Mountains?</h1>\n<p><strong>The Atlas Mountains peak at 4,167 meters (13,671 feet) on Mount Toubkal in the High Atlas Mountains. Start from Imlil trailhead for 1,800 meters gain. Reach Toubkal Refuge at 3,207 meters on day one. Summit push takes 4-6 hours. Berber Trail Culture demands sturdy gear like Hoka Speedgoat 6 boots.</strong> (52 words)</p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Category</th>\n<th>Specification</th>\n<th>Metric</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Peak Elevation</td>\n<td>Mount Toubkal (High Atlas)</td>\n<td>4,167m / 13,671ft</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Difficulty Level</td>\n<td>Expert scramble</td>\n<td>Grade IV (UIAA scale)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gear Requirement</td>\n<td>Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 review)</td>\n<td>290g/foot, 5mm drop</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Calories Burned</td>\n<td>Imlil to Summit</td>\n<td>6,500 kcal (avg 80kg)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Trail Time</td>\n<td>Azzaden Valley loop</td>\n<td>2 days / 28km</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Weight Carried</td>\n<td>Overnight pack</td>\n<td>8-10kg (water heavy)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>What Makes Mount Toubkal the True Height King?</h2>\n<p