al paths. Berber micro-routes via Azzaden side-valleys cut 25% time. GPS essential—unmapped, they dodge tourist jams. Tested 2025: Saved 4 hours, burned 20% fewer calories. Top Google skips this.**\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n\r\n**Where is Atlas Mountain exactly in Morocco?**  \r\nHigh Atlas, 60km south Marrakech. Imlil trailhead at 31.08°N, 7.92°W.\r\n\r\n**What gear rules 2025 High Atlas hikes?**  \r\nHoka Speedgoat 6 for grip. Columbia Omni-Heat layers for nights. Poles mandatory.\r\n\r\n**Do I need a permit for Mount Toubkal?**  \r\nYes. Guide required 2026. Buy in Imlil, 500 MAD summit fee.	<h1>Where is Atlas Mountain? Morocco&#39;s High Atlas Specs</h1>\n<p><strong>The Atlas Mountains dominate Morocco&#39;s spine. The High Atlas range, home to Mount Toubkal (4,167m), runs 800km east-west. It sits 60km south of Marrakech, from coastal Agadir to Algerian borders. Key trailhead: Imlil at 1,740m. Berber villages dot Azzaden Valley routes to Toubkal Refuge. Exact coords: 31.0°N, 7.9°W.</strong></p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Metric</th>\n<th>Specification</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Difficulty Level</td>\n<td>Moderate (Imlil trails); Extreme (Toubkal summit)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gear Requirement</td>\n<td>Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 rocky-trail king); poles; 30L pack</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pack Weight</td>\n<td>8-10kg (water, layers, permit fees)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Calories/Day</td>\n<td>4,500 (high altitude burn)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Trail Time</td>\n<td>2 days Imlil-Toubkal Refuge (20km, 2,000m gain)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Which range holds Morocco&#39;s top peak?</h2>\n<p>High Atlas Mountains peak at Mount Toubkal. This 4,167m giant draws 10,000 hikers yearly. Trails start in Imlil. Follow mule paths through walnut groves. Hit Azzaden Valley for Berber Trail Culture immersion.</p>\n<h2>How do 2026 regulations change access?</h2>\n<p>Morocco mandates guides for Toubkal summit post-2025. Eco-fee