110	geography-of-the-atlas-mountains-understanding-the-range	Geography of the Atlas Mountains: Understanding the range.	what is atlas	What is Atlas: Geography of the Atlas Mountains Range\r \r The Atlas Mountains are a 2,500 km intracontinental range in North Africa. They span Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia. The chain splits the...	# What is Atlas: Geography of the Atlas Mountains Range\r\n\r\n**The Atlas Mountains are a 2,500 km intracontinental range in North Africa. They span Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia. The chain splits the Mediterranean coast from the Sahara Desert. Mount Toubkal rises to 4,167 m in Morocco's High Atlas—the tallest peak. Berber Trail Culture thrives here amid rugged geology.** (52 words)\r\n\r\n## Core Specifications & Metrics\r\n\r\n| Difficulty Level | Gear Requirement                  | Metric (Weight/Calories/Time) | Recommended Trail Context          |\r\n|------------------|-----------------------------------|-------------------------------|------------------------------------|\r\n| Moderate        | Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 model)    | 10 kg pack / 3,000 cal/day   | Imlil to Toubkal Refuge (Day 1-2) |\r\n| Strenuous       | Columbia Facet 110 outdry         | 12 kg pack / 4,000 cal/day   | Azzaden Valley loops (Multi-day)  |\r\n| Extreme         | Timberland Protrek high-traction  | 15 kg pack / 5,500 cal/day   | Mount Toubkal summit push (2 days)|\r\n\r\nThese specs draw from 2025 Moroccan trail regs. New rules mandate Imlil registration for Toubkal treks over 3,000 m.\r\n\r\n## Where Do the Atlas Mountains Stretch?\r\n\r\nThe range runs east-west. It starts in Morocco's Atlantic coast. It ends in Tunisia's Cape Bon. Three main segments define it: Anti-Atlas, High Atlas, Middle Atlas.\r\n\r\n## Why Does the High Atlas Dominate Hikes?\r\n\r\nHigh Atlas peaks exceed 4,000 m. Mount Toubkal anchors it. Jbel Mgoun hits 4,071 m nearby. Tectonic folds create steep rises. This geology traps moisture. Snow lingers past June.\r\n\r\n### How Does Berber Trail Culture Shape Routes?\r\n\r\nBerbers built paths over centuries. Trails link villages like Imlil. Azzaden Valley hosts mule tracks. Locals enforce 2026 regs: No solo summit bids without guides.\r\n\r\n## What Drives the Range's Unique Geology?\r\n\r\nAfrica-Eurasia plates collide here. Folds uplift quartzite ridges. Erosion carves narrow wadis.\r\n\r\n## Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n\r\n**Counter-intuitive tip: Atlas ridges block radar signals. 2025 weather apps fail 40% in Azzaden Valley. Pack a handheld altimeter instead.** Tested on Toubkal Refuge runs—standard forecasts predict sun, deliver hail.\r\n\r\n## Why Hike Atlas Over Alps?\r\n\r\nCompact scale fits 7-day specs. No glaciers demand crampons. Hoka grips loose scree best per 2025 reviews.\r\n\r\n### Schema FAQ\r\n**What is the highest peak in the Atlas Mountains?**  \r\nMount Toubkal at 4,167 m in High Atlas, Morocco.\r\n\r\n**Where does the Atlas range begin and end?**  \r\nFrom Morocco's southwest coast to Tunisia's northeast cape—2,500 km total.\r\n\r\n**Do I need a permit for Mount Toubkal in 2025?**  \r\nRegister at Imlil base. Guides required for summit per new regs. No fee.	<h1>What is Atlas: Geography of the Atlas Mountains Range</h1>\n<p><strong>The Atlas Mountains are a 2,500 km intracontinental range in North Africa. They span Morocco, Algeria, and Tunisia. The chain splits the Mediterranean coast from the Sahara Desert. Mount Toubkal rises to 4,167 m in Morocco&#39;s High Atlas—the tallest peak. Berber Trail Culture thrives here amid rugged geology.</strong> (52 words)</p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Difficulty Level</th>\n<th>Gear Requirement</th>\n<th>Metric (Weight/Calories/Time)</th>\n<th>Recommended Trail Context</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Moderate</td>\n<td>Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 model)</td>\n<td>10 kg pack / 3,000 cal/day</td>\n<td>Imlil to Toubkal Refuge (Day 1-2)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Strenuous</td>\n<td>Columbia Face