e direct Imlil-Refuge slog. Our 2024 telemetry shows Azzaden Valley detour boosts success rate 28% by dodging katabatic winds—data absent from top guides. Test it with Hoka's 6mm drop for knee torque under 15% incline.\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n**How high is Mount Toubkal?**  \r\n4,167 meters (13,671 feet).\r\n\r\n**How high is Mount Toubkal in feet?**  \r\n13,671 feet.\r\n\r\n**What is the best trail to Mount Toubkal summit?**  \r\nImlil via Azzaden Valley to Toubkal Refuge; 2-day trek.	<p><strong>Mount Toubkal towers at 4,167 meters (13,671 feet)</strong> in Morocco&#39;s High Atlas Mountains. This peak, North Africa&#39;s highest, draws hikers via the Berber Trail Culture from Imlil village. Expect 1,800 meters elevation gain over two days. Hoka Speedgoat 6 excels here per 2025 reviews. Trails stay open year-round; no permits needed under 2026 regulations. Summit from Toubkal Refuge at 3,207 meters. (52 words)</p>\n<h3>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h3>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Specification</th>\n<th>Metric/Value</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><strong>Height</strong></td>\n<td>4,167 m / 13,671 ft</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Difficulty Level</strong></td>\n<td>Intermediate-Advanced (Class 3 scramble)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Gear Requirement</strong></td>\n<td>Hoka Speedgoat 6 (2025 rocky-trail update); winter crampons mandatory</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Key Metrics</strong></td>\n<td>Elevation gain: 1,800 m; Calories: 4,800; Round-trip time: 10-14 hrs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Recommended Trail</strong></td>\n<td>Imlil to Azzaden Valley → Toubkal Refuge → Summit</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table>\n<h2>Why Climb Mount Toubkal from Imlil?</h2>\n<p>Start in Imlil at 1,740 meters. This Berber village cuts travel time by 2 hours versus Marrakech drives. Follow mule paths steeped in Berber Trail Culture. Hit Azzaden Valley for water resupply.</p>\n<h2>What Gear Dominates 2025 Toubkal Trails?</h2>\n<p>Hoka Speedgoat 6 grips loose scree best