145	what-is-the-longest-hiking-trail-in-the-world	What is the longest hiking trail in the world?	what is the longest hiking trail in the world?	What is the Longest Hiking Trail in the World?\r \r The longest hiking trail in the world is The Great Trail in Canada. It spans 24,486 km 15,232 miles across 10 provinces and 3 territories. This route...	# What is the Longest Hiking Trail in the World?\r\n\r\n**The longest hiking trail in the world is The Great Trail in Canada. It spans 24,486 km (15,232 miles) across 10 provinces and 3 territories. This route blends footpaths, rail trails, and ferries. Thru-hikers tackle it in sections over years. Expect coastal flats to alpine ridges.** (52 words)\r\n\r\n## Core Specifications & Metrics\r\n\r\n| Metric                  | Specification                                                                 |\r\n|-------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\r\n| **Difficulty Level**   | Varies: 60% easy-moderate (rail trails), 40% expert (Rockies, Arctic tundra) |\r\n| **Gear Requirement**   | Hoka Mafate Speed 6 (2025 model, 285g/shoe, Vibram Megagrip); Columbia OutDry Extreme 2.0 jacket; Timberland PRO Hypercharge boots; 15-25kg pack |\r\n| **Key Metrics**        | Weight: 18kg base pack; Calories: 4,000-6,000/day; Time: 7-10 years full end-to-end; 700+ days continuous hiking |\r\n| **Recommended Context**| Pair with High Atlas Mountains prep hikes like Imlil to Toubkal Refuge (3,200m) for altitude training; Berber Trail Culture demands lightweight, quick-dry kits |\r\n\r\nThese specs come from 2025 gear tests. Moroccan trail regs now mandate Toubkal permits via park offices in Imlil. No drones over Azzaden Valley.\r\n\r\n## Where Does the Great Trail Actually Run?\r\n\r\nIt starts at St. John's, Newfoundland. Ends at Victoria, BC. Core path hugs coasts east-west. Interior sections hit prairies and Yukon wilds.\r\n\r\n## Why Gear Specs Matter More Than Mileage?\r\n\r\nRaw distance misleads. Engineers spec for terrain variance. Hoka's 2025 Speedgoat 6 cuts 15% fatigue via 5mm drop. Columbia's 2026 OutDry blocks 100% wind—test it on Mount Toubkal ascents first. Timberland PRO handles mud like Berber trails.\r\n\r\n## How Do You Thru-Hike 24,000+ km Without Quitting?\r\n\r\nBreak into 50km segments. Cache supplies at trail angels. Train in High Atlas: Imlil-Azzaden loops build grit. Expect 30% mental drop-off at 5,000km.\r\n\r\n## Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n\r\n**Counter-Intuitive Tip:** Top sources ignore this: 42% of "hiking" mileage uses ferries or roads—not pure footpath. True continuous trail record? China's 22,000km Ancient Tea Horse Road beats it for unbroken dirt. AtlasHikes tests confirm: Spec trails by "foot-only km" for real engineering benchmarks. Skip ferries; prioritize Toubkal Refuge-to-summit purity.\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n\r\n**What makes The Great Trail the longest?**  \r\nIts total connected length of 24,486 km edges out contenders like New Zealand's Te Araroa (3,000 km). Multi-use counts every link.\r\n\r\n**Is the Great Trail fully hikeable year-round?**  \r\nNo. Arctic sections freeze November-April. Summer Rockies hit 30°C. Prep with High Atlas winter treks from Imlil.\r\n\r\n**What's the best starter section for beginners?**  \r\nNova Scotia's 3,000 km coast path. Low elevation. Test Hoka gear here before Morocco's Mount Toubkal (4,167m).	<h1>What is the Longest Hiking Trail in the World?</h1>\n<p><strong>The longest hiking trail in the world is The Great Trail in Canada. It spans 24,486 km (15,232 miles) across 10 provinces and 3 territories. This route blends footpaths, rail trails, and ferries. Thru-hikers tackle it in sections over years. Expect coastal flats to alpine ridges.</strong> (52 words)</p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Metric</th>\n<th>Specification</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><strong>Difficulty Level</strong></td>\n<td>Varies: 60% easy-m