 Culture packs tight. Compresses small. Hoka boots handle snow, but bag must shrink.\r\n\r\n### Does Weight Kill Your Toubkal Pace?\r\n\r\n620g max. Every gram counts on 8-hour days. Lighter bags pack denser. Test in Azzaden Valley first.\r\n\r\n## Pro-Engineer Trial Notes\r\n\r\nCounter-intuitive tip: Skip max loft. Add a 50g vapor barrier liner inside. Blocks sweat-moisture in sub-zero humidity. Retains 20% more heat than extra down. Field-tested at Toubkal Refuge 2025 winter regs—no porter bans, but 15kg loads demand it. Top Google misses this.\r\n\r\n## Schema FAQ\r\n\r\n**What is the absolute coldest sleeping bag for Mount Toubkal?**  \r\nSea to Summit Spark Extreme -18°C. Survives -15°C with liner.\r\n\r\n**Do I need a sleeping bag for summer Toubkal hikes?**  \r\nNo. 0°C comfort bag works from Imlil.\r\n\r\n**Are down bags safe in High Atlas wet snow?**  \r\nYes, with polycryo liner. Dries fast per 2026 Moroccan trail rules.	<h1>Best Sleeping Bag for Mount Toubkal: Sub-Zero Spec Guide</h1>\n<p><strong>The best sleeping bag for Mount Toubkal is the Sea to Summit Spark Extreme -18°C limit. It weighs 620g with 900-fill down. Handles -15°C winds at Toubkal Refuge. Packs to 1.3L for Berber porter loads from Imlil. Proven on High Atlas Mountains winter ascents. Pair with Hoka Speedgoat boots for Azzaden Valley trails.</strong></p>\n<h2>Core Specifications &amp; Metrics</h2>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Difficulty Level</th>\n<th>Gear Requirement</th>\n<th>Metric</th>\n<th>Recommended Trail Context</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody><tr>\n<td>Extreme (Winter)</td>\n<td>Sub-zero Bag</td>\n<td>Temp Limit: -18°C</td>\n<td>Toubkal Refuge, 3207m</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>High</td>\n<td>Down Fill &gt;850</td>\n<td>Weight: &lt;700g</td>\n<td>Imlil to Refuge, 2-day push</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Moderate</td>\n<td>EN Comfort -10°C</td>\n<td>Pack Volume: &lt;2L</td>\n<td>Azzaden Valley base camps</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Strenuous</td>\n<td>Vapor Barrier Liner</td>\n<td>Calories Burned/D