 safety talk.", "accommodation": "Toubkal Refuge (heated)"}, {"day": "Day 2", "meals": "All meals", "title": "Acclimatization & Winter Skills", "duration": "4-5 hours training & trekking", "elevation": "Gain/lose 400m", "description": "Morning: winter mountaineering skills training - crampon use, ice axe technique, avalanche awareness. Afternoon: acclimatization snowshoe to nearby col with spectacular winter views. Return to refuge for early dinner and rest before summit attempt.", "accommodation": "Toubkal Refuge"}, {"day": "Day 3", "meals": "All meals", "title": "Winter Summit Attempt", "duration": "10-12 hours", "elevation": "Gain 960m, lose 2427m", "description": "Early start (4-5am) for summit bid. Headlamps illuminate snowy path. Crampons required for icy sections. Summit conditions depend on weather and snow stability. Incredible winter views if successful. Descend to refuge then continue to Imlil. Hot shower and celebration dinner.", "accommodation": "Hotel in Imlil"}, {"day": "Day 4", "meals": "Breakfast, lunch", "title": "Imlil Exploration & Return", "duration": "Half day + transfer", "elevation": "Minimal", "description": "Leisurely morning in Imlil. Optional easy snowshoe walk to nearby villages. Visit cooperatives for shopping. Lunch before transfer to Marrakech. Arrive afternoon.", "accommodation": "Not included"}]	["IFMGA-certified winter mountain guide", "Winter technical equipment (crampons, ice axe, snowshoes)", "3 nights accommodation (refuge + hotel)", "All meals during tour", "Winter safety equipment (avalanche transceiver, probe, shovel)", "Mule support to refuge (weather permitting)", "Winter mountaineering instruction", "Transfers from/to Marrakech", "Group first aid kit", "Water purification tablets"]	["Personal winter clothing and boots", "4-season sleeping bag (rental €15)", "Marrakech accommodation", "Travel insurance with winter sports coverage", "Tips for guide and team", "Personal expenses", "Alcoholic beverages"]	["Insulated mountaineering boots (rigid, crampon-compatible)", "4-season sleeping bag (-15°C comfort)", "Full winter layering system", "Insulated down jacket", "Waterproof/breathable shell layers", "Winter gloves (liner + insulated)", "Balaclava and warm hat", "Ski goggles for wind/snow", "Sunglasses with UV protection", "Trekking poles with snow baskets", "High-energy snacks for summit day", "Thermos for hot drinks", "Sunscreen SPF 50+ (snow reflection intense)", "Headlamp with spare batteries"]	December to April (depending on snow conditions)	Very challenging. Previous winter hiking experience strongly recommended. Summit not guaranteed due to weather/conditions. Good cardiovascular fitness required.	Winter trekking is quieter with fewer tourists. Refuge atmosphere is cozy and communal. Flexibility required for weather conditions.	6	classic	[{"id": 1, "date": "February 10, 2023", "name": "Lars Andersson", "rating": 5, "comment": "Epic winter adventure! Summiting Toubkal in snow was challenging but incredible. Our guide was excellent at assessing conditions and keeping us safe. The winter training day was valuable. Snowshoeing through silent, frozen valleys was magical. Different experience from summer - more technical but more rewarding. Proper gear essential!"}]	/routes/winter-toubkal-snowshoe-trek.geojson	\N
8	5-Day Summer Pastures Trek	berber-summer-pastures-trek	High Atlas Mountains	Trek to high-altitude summer pastures where Berber shepherds graze their flocks. Experience transhumance traditions and remote mountain life.	5	difficult	549	published	{https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960165/atlas-hikes/tours/8/0_1_qeeayd.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960165/atlas-hikes/tours/8/0_2_pj9lq4.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960166/atlas-hikes/tours/8/0_3_h24ktf.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960167/atlas-hikes/tours/8/0_tgzygi.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960167/atlas-hikes/tours/8/16ab709ac85_ujznn1.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960168/atlas-hikes/tours/8/16ab70addc6_uvsply.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960169/atlas-hikes/tours/8/16ab734aa96_fe9rpd.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960170/atlas-hikes/tours/8/16d6e9c2739_veyc8h.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960170/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1761bd7e4ec_r0vh1c.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960171/atlas-hikes/tours/8/178a255e3f3_twwljq.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960172/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1802259cb83_tgoykt.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960173/atlas-hikes/tours/8/180225a0be0_jkxpti.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960173/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1878466adfd_dflage.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960174/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1880d0331a5_h5l2ir.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960174/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1881070a18a_irzwhy.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960175/atlas-hikes/tours/8/18810727c36_j06shj.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960176/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1881072ef0c_atgkkm.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960177/atlas-hikes/tours/8/188aba2ea27_bakgkc.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960177/atlas-hikes/tours/8/188aba358cb_sno1gh.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960178/atlas-hikes/tours/8/188aba38181_mlkw7w.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960179/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1895e6138f3_v8vsoj.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960180/atlas-hikes/tours/8/18ab4114658_paescd.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960180/atlas-hikes/tours/8/18f4aa09394_bndrkj.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960181/atlas-hikes/tours/8/18f4aa0da15_oa7lb2.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960182/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1921591541a_dajme9.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960182/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1928202f515_1_fr4smy.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960183/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1928202f515_uwpqiz.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960184/atlas-hikes/tours/8/19644e24cee_qqpngl.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960184/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1987b078473_z8fgkg.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960185/atlas-hikes/tours/8/1987b07c2ca_erzldw.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960186/atlas-hikes/tours/8/198932f4370_tfdg3f.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960186/atlas-hikes/tours/8/198956df801_bdbm54.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960187/atlas-hikes/tours/8/198956e1f5e_vsgckf.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960187/atlas-hikes/tours/8/19897cd11f4_lv4zvp.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960188/atlas-hikes/tours/8/19897cd33b0_uxyswp.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960188/atlas-hikes/tours/8/19897cd4406_psxuoi.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960189/atlas-hikes/tours/8/19897cd7110_gnsgrr.jpg}	f	0	\N	2026-02-28 20:05:53.145695	2026-02-28 20:05:53.145695	["High mountain azib (summer shelters)", "Shepherd life experience", "Alpine meadows and wildlife", "Traditional cheese making", "Remote mountain passes", "Authentic camping and shepherding"]	[{"day": "Day 1", "meals": "Lunch, dinner", "title": "Imlil to Azib Tamsoulte", "duration": "5-6 hours trekking", "elevation": "Gain 900m", "description": "Trek from Imlil valley up to Azib Tamsoulte (2200m), a summer grazing area. Meet shepherd families who migrate here seasonally. Set up camp near their stone shelters. Evening: learn about transhumance traditions and mountain ecology.", "accommodation": "Mountain camping"}, {"day": "Day 2", "meals": "All meals", "title": "High Pastures & Shepherd Activities", "duration": "6-7 hours activities", "elevation": "Gain 600m, lose 200m", "description": "Join shepherds moving flocks to higher pastures. Learn traditional herding techniques and mountain navigation. Participate in milking and cheese-making. Afternoon: alpine meadow exploration and wildlife watching. Evening: stories around the fire.", "accommodation": "Mountain camping"}, {"day": "Day 3", "meals": "All meals", "title": "Cross to Remote Azib Likemt", "duration": "7-8 hours trekking", "elevation": "Gain 1000m, lose 800m", "description": "Trek over high mountain pass (3200m) to reach remote Azib Likemt. Pass through pristine alpine environment rarely visited. Set camp and meet another shepherd community. Learn about their seasonal lifestyle and challenges.", "accommodation": "Mountain camping"}, {"day": "Day 4", "meals": "All meals", "title": "Shepherd Skills & Mountain Life", "duration": "Activities day", "elevation": "Mountain level", "description": "Full day immersed in shepherd activities: making traditional butter, repairing shelters, collecting medicinal plants. Learn about mountain survival skills and weather prediction. Optional: help guard flocks from wildlife. Evening: traditional music.", "accommodation": "Azib shelter + camping"}, {"day": "Day 5", "meals": "Breakfast, lunch", "title": "Return to Imlil via Tizi Mzik", "duration": "6 hours trek + transfer", "elevation": "Lose 1100m", "description": "Trek back to civilization via scenic Tizi Mzik pass. Stop at permanent villages to see contrast with summer pasture life. Return to Imlil for hot shower and celebratory lunch. Transfer to Marrakech afternoon.", "accommodation": "Not included"}]	["Expert mountain guide (English/French/Berber)", "Shepherd community coordination", "Mule support for camping equipment", "All camping equipment (4-season tents)", "All meals (traditional mountain food + cheese)", "Cooking team", "Cultural activities and workshops", "Transfers from/to Marrakech"]	["Sleeping bag (can be rented €15)", "Personal trekking equipment", "Marrakech accommodation", "Travel insurance", "Tips for guide and team", "Personal expenses"]	["4-season sleeping bag (cold nights)", "Waterproof mountain boots", "Warm layers (fleece, down jacket)", "Rain gear", "Trekking poles", "Sun protection", "Personal medications", "Headlamp", "Water bottles (2L capacity)", "Camera for mountain landscapes"]	June to September (summer pasture season only)	Challenging high-altitude trekking. Good fitness essential. Experience with mountain camping helpful.	Unique opportunity to experience nomadic pastoralism. Respect for shepherd traditions essential. Physical participation welcome.	8	berber-villages	[{"id": 1, "date": "July 20, 2024", "name": "Patricia Green", "rating": 5, "comment": "Extraordinary cultural experience! Living alongside shepherds in high mountains was humbling. Learning cheese-making and helping with flocks gave real insight into this ancient lifestyle. The azib shelters and camping under stars was magical. Our guide translated shepherd stories beautifully. Challenging trek but worth every step."}]	/routes/berber-summer-pastures-trek.geojson	\N
17	3-Day Toubkal: The Scenic Azzaden & Aguelzim Traverse	toubkal-3day-azzaden-aguelzim	High Atlas Mountains, Toubkal National Park	Why take the direct path when a masterpiece of a trail awaits? This is the definitive Toubkal experience, crafted for those who believe the journey is as important as the destination. Over three days, we will guide you through the emerald Azzaden Valley, across the breathtakingly high Aguelzim ridge, and finally to the roof of North Africa. This is a challenging, high-altitude adventure that will show you the Atlas from its most dramatic and secluded perspectives.	3	difficult	289	published	{https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960067/atlas-hikes/tours/17/0_3_g7fn6g.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960067/atlas-hikes/tours/17/16d6e9c2739_mlcdqu.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960068/atlas-hikes/tours/17/18810727c36_ck9bl0.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960068/atlas-hikes/tours/17/1921591541a_ks6mou.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960069/atlas-hikes/tours/17/1928202f515_thtbcq.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960070/atlas-hikes/tours/17/19897cd11f4_ektn52.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960071/atlas-hikes/tours/17/20240512_164939_jl6jtw.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960072/atlas-hikes/tours/17/20240512_165509_x4vjnw.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960073/atlas-hikes/tours/17/20240513_093225_ftk0ag.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960075/atlas-hikes/tours/17/20240513_093300_zuipgz.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960076/atlas-hikes/tours/17/20240606_065002_c1umob.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960077/atlas-hikes/tours/17/20241105_083035_bvsgq5.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960078/atlas-hikes/tours/17/20241105_134921_kxkm8h.jpg}	t	0	\N	2026-02-28 20:05:53.156379	2026-02-28 20:05:53.156379	["Trek through the stunning, less-traveled Azzaden Valley, a jewel of the High Atlas.", "Cross the Tizi Mzik pass (2,489m) for spectacular views into two distinct valleys.", "Discover the powerful Ighouliden waterfalls, a hidden cascade deep in the mountains.", "Experience the epic high-altitude traverse of the Aguelzim ridge (3,650m).", "Conquer Mount Toubkal (4,167m) at sunrise, a truly unforgettable moment.", "Rest and recharge in traditional mountain refuges, sharing stories with fellow trekkers."]	[{"day": "Day 1", "meals": "Lunch, dinner", "title": "Imlil → Tizi Mzik → The Heart of the Azzaden Valley", "duration": "6-7 hours trekking", "elevation": "Gain 749m, lose 639m (net)", "description": "We leave Imlil behind, but instead of following the main crowd, we ascend the Tizi Mzik pass (2,489m). The reward is an immediate and breathtaking panorama of the Imlil valley we've left and the pristine Azzaden valley we are about to enter. We descend into a world of juniper forests and Berber terraces, making a short detour to the spectacular Ighouliden waterfalls. Our path then follows the valley floor, a lush green ribbon carved by the river, passing through friendly villages like Tizi Oussem. Our destination is Azib Tamsoult, a peaceful summer shepherd's hut nestled at the head of the valley, surrounded by towering peaks.", "accommodation": "Azib Tamsoult mountain refuge (gite)"}, {"day": "Day 2", "meals": "Breakfast, lunch, dinner", "title": "The Aguelzim Traverse → Toubkal Base Camp", "duration": "7-8 hours trekking", "elevation": "Gain 1,400m, lose 443m (net)", "description": "Today is an epic high-mountain journey. We leave the green valley behind and climb steadily up a rocky trail, entering a world of scree and sky. Our goal is the Aguelzim pass (3,650m), a high point on the very spine of the Atlas range. The view from here is unparalleled: the entire Toubkal massif is laid out before you in all its raw, granite glory. We then traverse the ridge before beginning the famous descent down the '99 zigzags' into the main Mizane Valley. This challenging path brings us to the bustling Toubkal Refuge (3,207m), where we'll rest, acclimatize, and prepare for our summit attempt.", "accommodation": "Toubkal Refuge (dormitory)"}, {"day": "Day 3", "meals": "Breakfast, lunch", "title": "Summit Day & The Long Descent to Imlil", "duration": "9-10 hours total", "elevation": "Gain 960m, descend 2,427m", "description": "The final push begins in the dark, long before dawn. We ascend by headlamp, the path growing steeper and rockier as we climb the south col. The final section involves some easy scrambling, but every step is worth it. We reach the summit cairn (4,167m) just as the first rays of sun illuminate the world. From this incredible vantage point, you can see the entire Atlas range and the vast expanse of the Sahara Desert to the south. After celebrating our achievement, we descend to the refuge for a well-earned breakfast, then continue our journey down through the valley, passing the sacred shrine of Sidi Chamharouch and the village of Aroumd before arriving back in Imlil, tired but triumphant.", "accommodation": "Not included"}]	["Professional, licensed English/French mountain guide", "Mule support for luggage (you carry only a daypack)", "2 nights mountain accommodation (refuge/gite)", "All meals during the trek (7 meals total)", "Toubkal National Park entry fees", "Emergency evacuation insurance"]	["Transport Marrakech-Imlil-Marrakech (can be arranged)", "Personal trekking gear (boots, poles, etc.)", "Sleeping bag (rental available for ~€10)", "Tips for guide and refuge staff (greatly appreciated)", "Personal travel insurance (highly recommended)", "Personal expenses (drinks, snacks at refuges)"]	["Broken-in, sturdy trekking boots", "Warm layers, including a fleece and down jacket (summit can be -5°C or colder)", "Waterproof jacket and pants", "Headlamp with spare batteries (essential for summit day)", "Sun protection (SPF 50+, hat, sunglasses, lip balm)", "Trekking poles (strongly recommended for the descent)", "1-2L water capacity or bladder", "Personal snacks and energy food", "30L daypack for summit day", "Toiletries and personal first-aid kit", "Camera/phone and power bank"]	April through October for the most stable and clear weather conditions.	This is a challenging trek requiring very good cardiovascular fitness and stamina. You will face long days with significant elevation gain, particularly on Day 2. Previous multi-day hiking experience at altitude is essential.	This route takes you through the heart of Berber territory, far from the main tourist trail. The Azzaden Valley is a place of authentic life and work. We ask that you dress modestly and be respectful of the local communities and their customs. The mountain refuges are basic but offer a warm, communal atmosphere and a unique chance to meet trekkers from around the world.	10	classic	[{"id": 1, "date": "September 12, 2024", "name": "Marcus Klein", "rating": 5, "comment": "What an adventure! The Azzaden route is so much better than the standard Toubkal approach. Day 2 over Aguelzim was tough but absolutely spectacular. Our guide Hassan was excellent, setting the perfect pace and sharing stories about Berber life. The 99 zigzags are real—my legs confirmed it! Summit sunrise was magical."}, {"id": 2, "date": "August 5, 2024", "name": "Emma Rodriguez", "rating": 5, "comment": "Perfect three-day itinerary for Toubkal. The Azzaden Valley is stunning and far less crowded than the main route. Loved staying in the mountain refuges and meeting other trekkers. The Aguelzim pass was challenging but the views made every step worth it. Highly recommend this route over the standard 2-day climb."}]	/routes/toubkal-3day-azzaden-aguelzim.geojson	\N
19	3-Day Ouanoukrim Ascent: The Ultimate 4000ers Challenge	ouanoukrim-ras-timesguida	Toubkal Massif, High Atlas	This is the definitive High Atlas mountaineering experience. Go beyond the standard Toubkal trek on this 3-day expedition designed for those who seek a greater challenge. We will guide you from the valley floor in Imlil to the summits of Morocco's second and third-highest peaks: Timesguida (4,089m) and Ras n-Ouanoukrim (4,083m). This journey involves thrilling scrambles, high-altitude camping, and the immense satisfaction of conquering a spectacular and demanding ridge traverse.	3	difficult	425	published	{https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960151/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_4_c0vrg8.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960151/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_6_t3viwe.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960152/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_7_vctxeq.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960153/atlas-hikes/tours/19/Ras_Timesguida1_hkngoz.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960153/atlas-hikes/tours/19/Ras_Timesguida2_q33bzd.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960154/atlas-hikes/tours/19/Ras_Timesguida3_lfjqoo.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960155/atlas-hikes/tours/19/Ras_Timesguida5_yl8myt.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960155/atlas-hikes/tours/19/Ras_Timesguida6_mqnkxc.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960156/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_1_i3vqjb.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960157/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_2_idj4vk.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960157/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_3_phgj5o.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960158/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_4_ccrauq.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960159/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_5_bydyhu.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960159/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_6_cjcxhv.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960160/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_7_oii00h.jpg,https://res.cloudinary.com/dmxhbqpjp/image/upload/v1774960161/atlas-hikes/tours/19/0_aonwsd.jpg}	t	0	\N	2026-02-28 20:05:53.158607	2026-02-28 20:05:53.158607	["Conquer two 4,000m+ summits in a single, epic push.", "Experience a thrilling, hands-on scramble along the spectacular Ouanoukrim ridge.", "A complete 3-day circuit, allowing for proper acclimatization and a safer ascent.", "Stand atop Timesguida (4,089m) and Ras n-Ouanoukrim (4,083m) with unparalleled views.", "Enjoy the camaraderie of two nights in the Toubkal Refuge, the heart of the High Atlas."]	[{"day": "Day 1", "meals": "Lunch, Dinner", "title": "Imlil to Toubkal Refuge: The Ascent Begins", "duration": "5-6 hours trekking", "elevation": "Gain 1,467 m (1,740 → 3,207 m)", "description": "Our expedition begins in Imlil (1,740m), the gateway to the High Atlas. After meeting our guide and muleteer team, we set off on the classic path towards the Toubkal Refuge. We'll follow the Mizane Valley, passing through the village of Aroumd and the sacred shrine of Sidi Chamharouch. The trek is a steady climb through stunning scenery, giving our bodies time to begin adjusting to the altitude. We'll arrive at the Toubkal Refuge (3,207m) in the afternoon, with time to rest, hydrate, and enjoy a hearty dinner while our guide provides a detailed briefing for tomorrow's main event.", "accommodation": "Toubkal Refuge (dormitory style)"}, {"day": "Day 2", "meals": "Breakfast, Packed Lunch, Dinner", "title": "Summit Day: The Ouanoukrim Ridge Traverse", "duration": "7-8 hours trekking", "elevation": "Gain/lose 880m", "description": "Today is the challenge we've been preparing for. We'll rise before dawn for an early breakfast, aiming to be on the trail as the first light appears. We leave the main Toubkal route and climb north towards the Tizi n'Ouagane pass. Here, the real adventure begins. We ascend the rocky spine of the Ouanoukrim ridge, a fantastic and exposed scramble that gets the adrenaline pumping. Our first summit is the plateau of Timesguida (4,089m), offering breathtaking views directly across to the face of Jbel Toubkal. We continue along the airy ridge to our second objective, the cairned summit of Ras n-Ouanoukrim (4,083m). After celebrating our achievement, we'll carefully retrace our steps and descend back to the refuge for a well-earned dinner and a deep, satisfying sleep.", "accommodation": "Toubkal Refuge (dormitory style)"}, {"day": "Day 3", "meals": "Breakfast, Lunch", "title": "Descent to Imlil & Reflection", "duration": "4-5 hours trekking", "elevation": "Lose 1,467 m (3,207 → 1,740 m)", "description": "After a leisurely breakfast and a final look at the mountains we've conquered, we begin our descent. The journey back to Imlil gives us a new perspective on the landscape we climbed just two days before. We'll retrace our steps through the Mizane Valley, passing Sidi Chamharouch and Aroumd, with plenty of time to stop for photos and reflect on the incredible achievement. We'll arrive back in Imlil in the afternoon, tired but triumphant, for our transfer back to Marrakech or your next adventure.", "accommodation": "Not included"}]	["Expert, certified mountain guide for the entire 3-day expedition", "Mules and muleteers to carry communal gear and food", "2 nights accommodation in the Toubkal Refuge (dormitory style)", "All meals during the trek (2 breakfasts, 3 lunches, 2 dinners, plus snacks)", "Technical guidance and safety management on all scrambling sections", "Toubkal National Park entry fees"]	["Transport to/from Imlil (we can help arrange this)", "Personal trekking gear (boots, poles, backpack, etc.)", "Sleeping bag (can be rented at the refuge for ~€10-15)", "Tips for guide and muleteers (a customary gesture of thanks is always appreciated)", "Personal travel insurance with mountain rescue coverage (mandatory)"]	["Sturdy, broken-in mountaineering boots with excellent ankle support", "Warm, non-cotton layering system: fleece, down jacket, thermal base layers", "A windproof and waterproof jacket and pants (the weather can change in an instant)", "Warm gloves, a hat/beanie, and a neck gaiter/buff", "High-SPF sun protection (sunscreen, lip balm, sunglasses)", "Trekking poles (highly recommended for the descent)", "Headlamp with extra batteries (essential for the early morning start)", "2L water capacity or bladder and high-energy snacks", "A 30L daypack for summit day"]	June through September for the most stable weather and minimal snow on the ridge.	Excellent physical fitness is required. This is a demanding high-altitude trek. You must be confident and comfortable scrambling on exposed rock for extended periods and have a very good head for heights. Previous multi-day hiking and experience at altitude is highly recommended.	This is a pure mountaineering objective in a sacred mountain environment. Our Berber guides have a deep respect for these peaks. We will move with purpose and respect, leaving no trace and appreciating the profound silence and power of this high-altitude world.	6	4000ers	[{"id": 1, "date": "August 23, 2024", "name": "Alex Kumar", "rating": 5, "comment": "Absolutely brilliant 3-day trip! The pace was perfect, allowing us to acclimatize before the big day. The Ouanoukrim ridge is way more interesting than Toubkal—the scrambling adds so much excitement and the views are phenomenal. Our guide knew every hand and foothold. If you're comfortable with scrambling, don't miss these summits."}]	/routes/ouanoukrim-ras-timesguida.geojson	\N
